result.execSummary:
The defendant Shade Alline Swayzer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Shade Alline Swayzer in court with attorney Richard J. Johnson.  Defendant Shade Alline Swayzer in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to negotiations, the State moved to dismiss but read in Counts 2 - 4.  Court granted Counts 2 - 4 dismissed but read in.

AS TO COUNT 01:
Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms.  Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  State needs time for victim notification; Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing before Branch 20 on 10/15/14 at 8:30 a.m.   Same bail; no remand.
/from Dr. Rawski dated 8/07/14, filed.
Court ordered cash bail reinstated at same amount.

Defendant Shade Alline Swayzer in court with attorney Richard J. Johnson.  Defendant Shade Alline Swayzer in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Doctor's report is received by all parties.  Court has colloquy with defendant regarding whether or not she feels she is competent to assist her attorney at this time; she stated that she is not; neither the State nor defense counsel challenge findings in report.  Court ordered defendant remanded to the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to provide transportation to the Department of Health Services for treatment to regain competency.  Court allowed 113 days time credit.  Review hearing to be set within 90 days to determine defendant's competency.  Hearing scheduled for November 5, 2014 at 08:30 am.
